  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVIDaction Resilient Health Systems</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Concern Worldwide - in partnership with Digital Health Solutions, mPower, and SAJIDA Foundation - aims to transform rural pharmacies into &#x201C;health hubs&#x201D; using the mCare and Digital Hospital platform, allowing remote care provision in the community. The platform is for local pharmacy owners to connect individuals remotely with primary health care doctors (supplied by Digital Healthcare Solutions). The platform leverages two apps:
 &#x2022; mCare: an open source mobile phone-based information system to enable front-line workers to collect data on clients, generate SMS reminders, and provide emergency medical support. mCare will be used as an e-learning app for pharmacists.
 &#x2022; Digital Hospital (formerly &#x201C;TONIC&#x201D;) was developed by Digital Health Solutions and adapted with funding from UKAID on the &#x201C;Essential Health Care for Disadvantaged Populations&#x201D; programme. Digital Hospital is a consumer app that will enable remote doctor consultations.</narrative>
  </description>
